<TITLE> Fakhruddin visits flood-hit Sirajganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, Aug 4 (bdnews24.com) -- Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed visited several flood-affected areas around Sirajganj Saturday and distributed relief among displaced people in the district town. Fakhruddin arrived at Chhatiantoli Karigarpara High School in the morning and distributed food, clothes and medicine among the flood hit local people. Later, the chief adviser spoke to reporters at Karigarpara High School. He said: "Flood-affected people from various low-lying sandbar areas around Sirajganj have already been moved to safer places where they have access to relief." "The army has been involved in ongoing rescue and relief operations in coordination with the local and district administrations," he added. Fakhruddin assured the local people that the government was committed to providing a comprehensive and coordinated programme of relief for all those affected by the floods. "A decision on whether to accept foreign assistance will be taken at a meeting of the advisory council Saturday afternoon," he said. "However, foreign assistance has already started arriving. Different donor agencies are now assisting flood-affected people through their ongoing development projects." The advisor added that a special fund was being set up from Sunday by the chief adviser's office to provide members of the public an official way to contribute. Details would be published soon, he said. Disaster management adviser Tapan Chowdhury and senior army officers accompanied the chief adviser. bdnews24.c
